117
00:12:54.336 --> 00:12:55.791 line:82%
How can you wake up,
if you never sleep?

118
00:12:55.874 --> 00:12:59.292 line:82%
You're late for the graduation
ceremony. Hurry.

119
00:13:04.780 --> 00:13:06.545 line:82%
Is it a holiday?

120
00:13:13.557 --> 00:13:16.297 line:82%
Fancy being late for graduation,
Raj!

121
00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:18.253 line:82%
No choice. Last night...

122
00:13:21.057 --> 00:13:22.916 line:82%
What's with him?
Has he been drinking?

123
00:13:22.999 --> 00:13:28.336 line:82%
Apparently someone's failed,
It'll be announced in public.

124
00:13:32.848 --> 00:13:34.472 line:82%
- Best of luck.
- Oh, God!

125
00:13:34.555 --> 00:13:37.695 line:82%
Listen, best of luck.

126
00:13:39.033 --> 00:13:41.857 line:82%
And for the first time in the history
of this university

127
00:13:42.110 --> 00:13:46.192 line:82%
we have a failure.
Raj Malhotra.

128
00:13:56.162 --> 00:13:59.799 line:82%
I'm proud of you, my son.
I'm really proud of you!

129
00:13:59.882 --> 00:14:03.586 line:82%
Son, you've brought honor to me,
Dharam Veer Malhotra.

130
00:14:06.531 --> 00:14:08.753 line:82%
You didn't hear it right, Pops.

131
00:14:09.875 --> 00:14:12.201 line:82%
I knew you'd make my name shine.

132
00:14:12.544 --> 00:14:16.044 line:82%
The whole family is proud
of you today.

133
00:14:16.667 --> 00:14:18.628 line:82%
See how they smile on you.

134
00:14:19.193 --> 00:14:23.378 line:82%
Your great-grandfather, Diwan Brijnath,
never went to school.

135
00:14:25.305 --> 00:14:28.710 line:82%
My grandfather, Diwan Dwarkanath,
failed fourth grade.

136
00:14:29.472 --> 00:14:33.741 line:82%
My father, Diwan Pushkarnath,
failed eighth grade.

137
00:14:33.952 --> 00:14:36.328 line:82%
And I, your father,
failed matriculation.

138
00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:40.402 line:82%
Failing is a tradition
in our family.

139
00:14:40.602 --> 00:14:45.026 line:82%
Glad you respect this tradition.
But you did even better.

140
00:14:45.109 --> 00:14:48.545 line:82%
We all failed in India.
You failed in London.

141
00:14:52.956 --> 00:14:54.082 line:82%
Pops, are you really happy?

142
00:14:54.275 --> 00:14:55.833 line:82%
Happy? I'm delighted.

143
00:14:55.916 --> 00:15:00.721 line:82%
Studying is pointless.
Doesn't fill your pockets.

144
00:15:00.804 --> 00:15:03.600 line:82%
Take me. I was illiterate
when I left Bhatinda.

145
00:15:03.683 --> 00:15:05.793 line:82%
Now I'm a London millionaire.

146
00:15:05.876 --> 00:15:07.335 line:82%
- Yo, Pops.
- Thank you.

147
00:15:07.418 --> 00:15:09.210 line:82%
Everything happens for the best.

148
00:15:09.293 --> 00:15:11.128 line:82%
Tomorrow you can start
at the office.

149
00:15:11.211 --> 00:15:13.370 line:82%
- The office, Pops?
- Today, if you like.

150
00:15:13.453 --> 00:15:15.917 line:82%
- Not tomorrow either.
- Why not?

151
00:15:16.417 --> 00:15:21.378 line:82%
Pops! You're a man of experience.
You know how hard it is to fail.

152
00:15:21.630 --> 00:15:25.353 line:82%
I've been working so hard at it,
I need rest.

153
00:15:26.019 --> 00:15:29.132 line:82%
Say a long holiday
in Europe. Cheers!

154
00:15:29.215 --> 00:15:32.750 line:82%
- A holiday. How long?
- A month or so.

155
00:15:32.833 --> 00:15:37.209 line:82%
A month or so? Hold this
and turn around.

156
00:15:37.292 --> 00:15:39.836 line:82%
- Surprise present, Pops?
- Yes, surprise.

157
00:15:41.290 --> 00:15:43.961 line:82%
Moron! Is this what I deserve?

158
00:15:52.117 --> 00:15:54.042 line:82%
Don't break that.

159
00:16:02.903 --> 00:16:04.608 line:82%
You OK, Pops?

160
00:16:10.495 --> 00:16:14.500 line:82%
You're right, Pops. I should
take care of your business.

161
00:16:14.897 --> 00:16:18.661 line:82%
- You're getting old now.
- The hell I am!

162
00:16:18.744 --> 00:16:20.734 line:82%
Exactly, Pops.

163
00:16:21.648 --> 00:16:22.930 line:82%
- Continue...
- Yes.

164
00:16:23.013 --> 00:16:25.966 line:82%
I've decided. No Europe. I'll start
work tomorrow.

165
00:16:26.049 --> 00:16:29.669 line:82%
In this house only your father
makes decisions.

166
00:16:30.036 --> 00:16:33.150 line:82%
I've made up my mind.
You'll go to Europe.

167
00:16:33.233 --> 00:16:37.961 line:82%
No, Pops. I've had it too easy.
My days of youth are over.

168
00:16:39.125 --> 00:16:42.152 line:82%
Never say they're over.

169
00:16:44.232 --> 00:16:47.818 line:82%
I've slogged all my life so you
could do...

170
00:16:48.417 --> 00:16:51.378 line:82%
whatever I couldn't.

171
00:16:54.721 --> 00:16:58.003 line:82%
I never knew when my youth
came or went.

172
00:16:59.473 --> 00:17:04.377 line:82%
But I didn't mind. I knew my son
would enjoy youth for me.

173
00:17:05.577 --> 00:17:08.961 line:82%
If you think you've had
enough fun

174
00:17:09.963 --> 00:17:13.753 line:82%
and the days of youth
are behind you, never mind.

175
00:17:14.960 --> 00:17:19.325 line:82%
Go to Europe. Live my youth
for me.

176
00:17:19.998 --> 00:17:21.169 line:82%
Pops...

177
00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:26.336 line:82%
you'e the greatest.

178
00:17:27.542 --> 00:17:30.544 line:82%
- You are also ok.
- Thank you.

179
00:17:33.630 --> 00:17:35.252 line:82%
- Shut up.
- Sorry.

180
00:17:36.208 --> 00:17:37.250 line:82%
I love you.

181
00:17:38.624 --> 00:17:39.671 line:82%
Thank you.

182
00:17:43.209 --> 00:17:44.333 line:82%
Ajit's letter!

183
00:17:50.333 --> 00:17:53.998 line:82%
Lajjo! Look what's here.

184
00:17:54.132 --> 00:17:55.990 line:82%
A letter from my friend.

185
00:17:56.073 --> 00:17:58.958 line:82%
- Alright.
- From Ajit.

186
00:17:59.041 --> 00:18:01.462 line:82%
Go on, smell it.

187
00:18:03.379 --> 00:18:05.107 line:82%
The fragrance of Punjab!

188
00:18:05.368 --> 00:18:06.376 line:82%
It indeed is.

189
00:18:06.472 --> 00:18:09.294 line:82%
The smell of mustard spinach
and cornbread.

190
00:18:09.377 --> 00:18:11.846 line:82%
Long kurtas, short pants.

191
00:18:11.929 --> 00:18:14.598 line:82%
- Cornbread, mustard spinach!
- Oh, God!

192
00:18:14.681 --> 00:18:16.125 line:82%
My dear friend Baldev,

193
00:18:16.917 --> 00:18:18.416 line:82%
we are all well.

194
00:18:18.499 --> 00:18:22.960 line:82%
We pray to God that you and
your family are well too.

195
00:18:23.410 --> 00:18:26.834 line:82%
You'll be pleased to hear
my son Kuljit has got his BA.

196
00:18:26.917 --> 00:18:29.252 line:82%
He is now working with me.

197
00:18:29.542 --> 00:18:34.711 line:82%
The time has come for our
friendship to turn to kinship.

198
00:18:35.208 --> 00:18:39.044 line:82%
The promise we made 20 years ago
must be fulfilled now.

199
00:18:39.458 --> 00:18:43.961 line:82%
You must come home so Kuljit
and Simran can be married...

200
00:18:45.417 --> 00:18:46.586 line:82%
Go on.

201
00:18:50.458 --> 00:18:53.625 line:82%
She's feeling shy.

202
00:18:53.708 --> 00:18:58.377 line:82%
See, Lajjo? That's our upbringing.
Our culture.

203
00:18:58.733 --> 00:19:01.545 line:82%
My daughter still feels shy
in front of her father.

204
00:19:02.000 --> 00:19:04.294 line:82%
This means I haven't failed

205
00:19:04.583 --> 00:19:09.077 line:82%
to keep the soul of India
alive while in London.

206
00:19:09.608 --> 00:19:14.252 line:82%
Our daughter is engaged. Don't just
stand there. Let's celebrate.

207
00:19:15.102 --> 00:19:17.859 line:82%
- Chutki, I'm so happy.
- Can I say one thing?

208
00:19:18.460 --> 00:19:20.731 line:82%
Not one, you can say four.

209
00:19:21.292 --> 00:19:23.854 line:82%
Shouldn't you consult Simran?

210
00:19:24.250 --> 00:19:28.773 line:82%
She's known since childhood
she was engaged to Kuljit.

211
00:19:28.982 --> 00:19:32.279 line:82%
She may have known, but
after all these years...

212
00:19:32.542 --> 00:19:33.833 line:82%
Don't you worry.

213
00:19:34.167 --> 00:19:39.211 line:82%
Simran will be so happy.
You'll have to cast off the evil eye.

214
00:19:40.305 --> 00:19:42.461 line:82%
I'll write to Ajit tomorrow.

215
00:19:42.940 --> 00:19:46.044 line:82%
Oh, Lord! The day has
finally come.

216
00:20:00.875 --> 00:20:02.710 line:82%
What are you doing, Simran?

217
00:20:05.708 --> 00:20:10.003 line:82%
I forgot, Ma. I have no right
to dream.

218
00:20:10.667 --> 00:20:14.711 line:82%
No, child. Dream away.
You must dream.

219
00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:17.711 line:82%
Just don't count on
dreams coming true.

220
00:20:20.792 --> 00:20:24.252 line:82%
Who knows? Kuljit may be
your dream.

221
00:20:26.167 --> 00:20:29.559 line:82%
I've booked the tickets and you're
coming to Europe with me.

222
00:20:29.642 --> 00:20:30.833 line:82%
- I can't.
- Shut up!

