01:56:53.261 --> 01:56:54.442 line:82%
We'll have a blast!

1127
01:56:55.442 --> 01:56:57.151 line:82%
Aren't you going?

1128
01:56:58.775 --> 01:57:01.901 line:82%
Hurry, on the double.
And get some Black Label.

1129
01:57:01.984 --> 01:57:04.486 line:82%
We'll have some Scotch whisky.

1130
01:57:09.026 --> 01:57:11.191 line:82%
- Cheers.
- Pass me the lighter.

1131
01:57:16.692 --> 01:57:20.619 line:82%
We're deeply indebted to you
for saving Kuljit's life.

1132
01:57:20.702 --> 01:57:25.069 line:82%
- No, Maaji. It was my duty.
- May you live long, son.

1133
01:57:27.192 --> 01:57:29.901 line:82%
Preeti, some sweets for Raj.

1134
01:57:31.233 --> 01:57:32.334 line:82%
Thank you.

1135
01:57:37.737 --> 01:57:38.860 line:82%
That's enough.

1136
01:57:40.151 --> 01:57:42.608 line:82%
10 million pounds?
Why didn't you say so?

1137
01:57:43.358 --> 01:57:46.699 line:82%
Raj, my son!

1138
01:57:46.984 --> 01:57:48.740 line:82%
- Give him the sweets!
- I have some already.

1139
01:57:48.823 --> 01:57:50.271 line:82%
Have some from me.

1140
01:57:50.348 --> 01:57:54.354 line:82%
That's it! You want to build
a factory? We'll get it done.

1141
01:57:56.067 --> 01:57:58.441 line:82%
Get ready for a party
at Baldev's.

1142
01:57:58.524 --> 01:58:01.735 line:82%
- Baldev?
- A dear friend of mine.

1143
01:58:02.443 --> 01:58:05.027 line:82%
Kuljit is marrying his daughter.

1144
01:58:07.674 --> 01:58:11.941 line:82%
- What will I do there?
- He's right. What will he do?

1145
01:58:12.024 --> 01:58:16.361 line:82%
- But if you insist...
- That's my boy!

1146
01:58:17.899 --> 01:58:22.194 line:82%
But Baldev is an English type.
We can't be late.

1147
01:58:22.731 --> 01:58:24.484 line:82%
That's my boy!

1148
01:58:24.859 --> 01:58:27.734 line:82%
Come on. We're always late
because of you.

1149
01:58:28.359 --> 01:58:30.083 line:82%
Kuljit, I need to talk to you.

1150
01:58:30.166 --> 01:58:33.226 line:82%
- Don't worry, you'll be fine.
- Sure, no problem.

1151
01:58:37.355 --> 01:58:39.535 line:82%
I'll have them all. Thank you

1152
01:58:48.691 --> 01:58:50.275 line:82%
Welcome.

1153
01:58:55.316 --> 01:58:56.803 line:82%
My respects, Father-in-law.

1154
01:59:01.413 --> 01:59:02.691 line:82%
Congratulations!

1155
01:59:18.316 --> 01:59:19.400 line:82%
Listen.

1156
01:59:23.388 --> 01:59:24.858 line:82%
The mean shopkeeper.

1157
01:59:26.650 --> 01:59:27.775 line:82%
Hello, how are you?

1158
01:59:28.858 --> 01:59:34.108 line:82%
- I've seen you before.
- Me? I never leave the house.

1159
01:59:34.816 --> 01:59:40.089 line:82%
London? I never got beyond
Ludhiana or the Punjab border.

1160
01:59:40.172 --> 01:59:42.943 line:82%
This is my friend Raj,
just arrived from London.

1161
01:59:45.808 --> 01:59:49.485 line:82%
Oh, here you are, Raj! He saved my
Kuljit's life.

1162
01:59:50.496 --> 01:59:55.027 line:82%
Know who he is? My dearest
and oldest friend, and my in-law.

1163
01:59:56.608 --> 01:59:58.444 line:82%
Don't stare! Pay your respects.

1164
01:59:59.983 --> 02:00:02.864 line:82%
The doctor is waiting to meet you.

1165
02:00:05.153 --> 02:00:07.402 line:82%
The doctor is a gem.

1166
02:00:08.733 --> 02:00:11.022 line:82%
The old geezer has an
amazing memory.

1167
02:00:11.105 --> 02:00:12.634 line:82%
- What happened?
- Nothing.

1168
02:00:12.717 --> 02:00:16.569 line:82%
Amazing! This old mansion
is amazing. Let's go.

1169
02:00:22.310 --> 02:00:25.360 line:82%
This is my friend Raj.
He's from London, too.

1170
02:00:26.090 --> 02:00:27.652 line:82%
And this is Simran...

1171
02:00:30.423 --> 02:00:31.860 line:82%
Hello, Simran.

1172
02:00:32.441 --> 02:00:37.569 line:82%
You know, if it wasn't for him,
today we may not...

1173
02:00:38.008 --> 02:00:39.025 line:82%
What are you saying?

1174
02:00:39.108 --> 02:00:41.485 line:82%
Where in London do you stay, Mr. Raj?

1175
02:00:41.941 --> 02:00:42.985 line:82%
Tell her.

1176
02:00:44.608 --> 02:00:49.361 line:82%
- I live in Hampstead, miss...
- Miss Rajeshwari.

1177
02:00:50.816 --> 02:00:54.694 line:82%
I'm very pleased to meet you,
Miss Rajeshwari.

1178
02:00:55.141 --> 02:01:01.528 line:82%
- What's this?
- A small gift for a small bride.

1179
02:01:02.608 --> 02:01:06.486 line:82%
This is so sweet.
Thank you, Mr. Raj.

1180
02:01:06.738 --> 02:01:08.692 line:82%
You're most welcome Miss Rajeshwari.

1181
02:01:10.650 --> 02:01:15.194 line:82%
The people that I like usually
call me Chutki.

1182
02:01:15.733 --> 02:01:17.110 line:82%
Ok, Chutki.

1183
02:01:17.733 --> 02:01:22.861 line:82%
And the people I like
may call me Raj. Just Raj.

1184
02:01:23.233 --> 02:01:25.944 line:82%
- Alright, Raj.
- Alright.

1185
02:01:39.233 --> 02:01:41.319 line:82%
This is my British friend, Raj.

1186
02:01:41.696 --> 02:01:45.193 line:82%
- I told you about him.
- Bless you, son.

1187
02:01:46.631 --> 02:01:49.111 line:82%
- Have some.
- Thank you, Maaji.

1188
02:01:50.725 --> 02:01:52.775 line:82%
Allow me, Maaji. I'll pass it round.

1189
02:01:52.858 --> 02:01:56.162 line:82%
You're from the groom's side.
You're our guest.

1190
02:01:57.400 --> 02:01:58.985 line:82%
You're amazing, Maaji.

1191
02:01:59.528 --> 02:02:03.124 line:82%
First you call me son, now you
treat me as an outsider.

1192
02:02:12.483 --> 02:02:15.903 line:82%
I made the lassi with my own
hands for all the aunties.

1193
02:02:19.108 --> 02:02:21.069 line:82%
I love your sari.

1194
02:02:26.650 --> 02:02:27.901 line:82%
After you.

1195
02:02:36.506 --> 02:02:39.608 line:82%
No! Let the young people do that.

1196
02:02:39.691 --> 02:02:42.108 line:82%
That's what I say, but who listens?

1197
02:02:42.400 --> 02:02:44.902 line:82%
- They dump all the work on me.
- That's what I say.

1198
02:02:45.941 --> 02:02:48.358 line:82%
- Who are you?
- Me? I'm Raj.

1199
02:02:48.441 --> 02:02:50.110 line:82%
Raj! Raj who?

1200
02:02:50.391 --> 02:02:51.902 line:82%
Your future son-in-law.

1201
02:02:52.465 --> 02:02:55.652 line:82%
Your future son-in-law's
close friend.

1202
02:02:55.900 --> 02:02:58.607 line:82%
Sweet boy! Put it over there.

1203
02:02:59.483 --> 02:03:01.027 line:82%
Sweetheart!

1204
02:03:06.233 --> 02:03:08.027 line:82%
Today is a lucky day.

1205
02:03:08.645 --> 02:03:13.235 line:82%
I saw Simran laugh
for the first time.

1206
02:03:22.560 --> 02:03:24.069 line:82%
You're right, Mother.

1207
02:03:24.525 --> 02:03:28.971 line:82%
Simran is looking very happy
today. Congratulations.

1208
02:03:40.775 --> 02:03:42.027 line:82%
Sir, beer?

1209
02:03:42.983 --> 02:03:44.736 line:82%
Lassi? This is a lassi, sir...

1210
02:03:46.025 --> 02:03:49.694 line:82%
Sweet lassi? No? Plain, then.

1211
02:03:53.900 --> 02:03:59.193 line:82%
Raj, you won't make it.
Book your ticket home.

1212
02:05:04.858 --> 02:05:06.872 line:82%
English boy! Get up.

1213
02:05:07.650 --> 02:05:10.319 line:82%
Aren't you coming? Hunting?

1214
02:05:13.983 --> 02:05:17.200 line:82%
Come off it, Raj. Get up!

1215
02:05:17.283 --> 02:05:19.900 line:82%
I'm ill. I have a fever.

1216
02:05:19.983 --> 02:05:23.402 line:82%
I was so cold last night, I went
to bed with my shoes on.

1217
02:05:23.608 --> 02:05:27.527 line:82%
- You have only one shoe on.
- That's my cold foot.

1218
02:05:27.858 --> 02:05:31.819 line:82%
I'm very sorry I can't go hunting
with you.

1219
02:05:32.233 --> 02:05:35.942 line:82%
Don't worry. You British
are so feeble.

1220
02:05:36.025 --> 02:05:38.775 line:82%
I'll send some medicine.
You'll be better by tonight.

1221
02:05:38.858 --> 02:05:40.317 line:82%
We're having fowl tonight.

1222
02:05:40.400 --> 02:05:41.860 line:82%
Don't worry, you'll be alright.

1223
02:05:43.525 --> 02:05:46.569 line:82%
- Best of luck.
- Thank you.

1224
02:05:46.945 --> 02:05:48.235 line:82%
Idiot.

1225
02:05:48.941 --> 02:05:51.481 line:82%
Raj, now you better start.

1226
02:05:53.150 --> 02:05:56.944 line:82%
- What's all this?
- Keep moving.

1227
02:05:59.695 --> 02:06:02.108 line:82%
Something amazing happened.

1228
02:06:02.191 --> 02:06:07.025 line:82%
I happened to bump into Father's
childhood friend.

1229
02:06:07.108 --> 02:06:10.775 line:82%
He gave me all this.
Here, let me hold it.

1230
02:06:10.858 --> 02:06:15.111 line:82%
But what can I do with all this
wheat and sugar?

1231
02:06:15.984 --> 02:06:18.736 line:82%
You're having a wedding.
Might come in handy.

1232
02:06:19.874 --> 02:06:23.069 line:82%
The bride's family can't
accept presents from you.

1233
02:06:23.350 --> 02:06:26.525 line:82%
Maaji, not again. Decide.

1234
02:06:26.608 --> 02:06:30.317 line:82%
If you call me "son," then you
must treat me as a son.

1235
02:06:30.861 --> 02:06:33.568 line:82%
- How's that?
- No arguing with sons.

1236
02:06:34.316 --> 02:06:37.110 line:82%
- OK, I won't.
- That's more like it.

1237
02:06:37.661 --> 02:06:41.525 line:82%
Now listen to this.
My mother used to say

1238
02:06:41.608 --> 02:06:45.776 line:82%
boys who help out at weddings
marry lovely brides.

1239
02:06:47.316 --> 02:06:49.860 line:82%
Is that why you're helping?

1240
02:06:50.275 --> 02:06:52.485 line:82%
Only the lucky get
a good bride these days.

1241
02:06:53.191 --> 02:06:54.293 line:82%
What's a good bride?

1242
02:06:59.400 --> 02:07:02.896 line:82%
Let's say this.
She must have shades of you.

1243
02:07:04.525 --> 02:07:06.524 line:82%
Don't tick me off. Bless me.

1244
02:07:06.607 --> 02:07:08.984 line:82%
You'll get the bride
of your choice.

1245
02:07:09.715 --> 02:07:13.068 line:82%
- I must be off.
- Open this for me, please.

1246
02:07:13.275 --> 02:07:14.693 line:82%
Of course, I'll...

1247
02:07:20.311 --> 02:07:24.192 line:82%
Don't think about it too much,
just buy it.

1248
02:07:24.275 --> 02:07:26.617 line:82%
You won't find such workmanship
in Delhi or Mumbai.

1249
02:07:26.893 --> 02:07:30.318 line:82%
All the girls will be jealous
of you.

1250
02:07:30.525 --> 02:07:32.359 line:82%
As for the boys...

1251
02:07:33.025 --> 02:07:34.567 line:82%
It's lovely.

1252
02:07:41.275 --> 02:07:44.943 line:82%
It's not that special.
Show me... that one!

1253
02:07:46.983 --> 02:07:50.608 line:82%
Here, that's a beautiful piece.
Just look at it.

1254
02:07:50.691 --> 02:07:52.811 line:82%
It'll make you glow.

1255
02:07:54.816 --> 02:07:59.172 line:82%
Dreadful saris. I want something
special for the wedding.

1256
02:08:01.566 --> 02:08:03.191 line:82%
Look at this one.

1257
02:08:03.274 --> 02:08:06.526 line:82%
I'll lose my reputation if you
don't look good in this.

1258
02:08:06.899 --> 02:08:10.925 line:82%
Made with real gold thread.
You shimmer.

1259
02:08:11.268 --> 02:08:14.693 line:82%
Stop this nonsense.
I don't like it.

1260
02:08:18.941 --> 02:08:21.944 line:82%
I suppose it's not that bad.

1261
02:08:22.550 --> 02:08:23.901 line:82%
I'll keep it.

1262
02:08:29.566 --> 02:08:31.735 line:82%
Pack it. Don't overcharge.

1263
02:08:32.983 --> 02:08:35.284 line:82%
Exhausting, all these saris.

1264
02:08:35.558 --> 02:08:39.944 line:82%
One grain, two grains.
Grain upon grain.

1265
02:08:47.715 --> 02:08:52.194 line:82%
The girl dances on the roof.
The boy is crazy.

1266
02:09:07.350 --> 02:09:10.755 line:82%
- Raj, sing us a song.
- I can't sing.

1267
02:09:10.838 --> 02:09:12.745 line:82%
Don't be coy like a girl. Sing.

1268
02:09:13.540 --> 02:09:14.902 line:82%
Go on, sing.

1269
02:09:15.976 --> 02:09:17.069 line:82%
Please.

1270
02:09:18.426 --> 02:09:21.015 line:82%
If you're in love,
what is there to fear?

1271
02:09:21.216 --> 02:09:24.734 line:82%
If you're in love,
what is there to fear?

1272
02:09:35.528 --> 02:09:40.068 line:82%
Live and die by love.
That's all

1273
02:09:46.858 --> 02:09:50.743 line:82%
You eye one girl
and aim at another

1274
02:09:55.358 --> 02:09:57.113 line:82%
Let it drop

1275
02:09:57.196 --> 02:09:59.735 line:82%
What will you sing now?

1276
02:10:07.975 --> 02:10:13.152 line:82%
The brave of heart will come to
take the bride away

1277
02:10:18.191 --> 02:10:23.794 line:82%
And everyone in the house
will be left gawking

1278
02:10:37.818 --> 02:10:41.233 line:82%
- Simran, listen.
- They're sitting right there. Let go.

1279
02:10:41.316 --> 02:10:44.900 line:82%
- On one condition. A kiss, Senorita.
- You nuts?

1280
02:10:44.983 --> 02:10:46.444 line:82%
Just one kiss.

1281
02:10:47.125 --> 02:10:48.568 line:82%
Ma will see us.

1282
02:10:51.173 --> 02:10:52.276 line:82%
Let her.

1283
02:10:54.183 --> 02:10:57.401 line:82%
- Chutki will see us.
- Let her.

1284
02:10:59.733 --> 02:11:02.815 line:82%
- My aunt will see us.
- Let her.

1285
02:11:14.456 --> 02:11:17.561 line:82%
Her dear father will be
the end of me.

1286
02:11:21.233 --> 02:11:24.943 line:82%
Stop thinking, Baldev.
You can't win.

1287
02:11:25.316 --> 02:11:28.943 line:82%
For the first time in 20 years,
I'll beat you.

1288
02:11:30.441 --> 02:11:35.652 line:82%
That was a good move.
I think I've lost this time.

1289
02:11:41.403 --> 02:11:43.576 line:82%
Brilliant!

1290
02:11:48.580 --> 02:11:53.652 line:82%
- I'll put it back.
- Wait. Let me see.

1291
02:11:55.691 --> 02:11:58.933 line:82%
You are a genius. You're not only
genius you're indigenous.

1292
02:12:19.567 --> 02:12:20.570 line:82%
What's wrong?

1293
02:12:23.775 --> 02:12:25.733 line:82%
You know what's happening
tomorrow?

1294
02:12:25.816 --> 02:12:27.694 line:82%
No. What?

1295
02:12:30.025 --> 02:12:32.306 line:82%
I'm getting engaged to Kuljit.

1296
02:12:32.389 --> 02:12:35.118 line:82%
Oh yes! Congratulations.

1297
02:12:36.900 --> 02:12:38.026 line:82%
Be serious Raj.

1298
02:12:41.476 --> 02:12:46.068 line:82%
Kuljit will make me wear
his ring on this finger.

1299
02:12:48.570 --> 02:12:52.423 line:82%
Know why an engagement ring
is worn on this finger?

1300
02:12:56.006 --> 02:12:59.859 line:82%
Because the veins from this finger
go straight to the heart.

1301
02:13:03.276 --> 02:13:06.018 line:82%
I can only wear your ring, Raj.

1302
02:13:06.808 --> 02:13:12.280 line:82%
Want me to put a ring
on your finger in full view?

1303
02:13:12.363 --> 02:13:13.526 line:82%
No problem.

1304
02:13:14.500 --> 02:13:19.069 line:82%
It's all a joke to you. You don't
know what I'm going through.

1305
02:13:19.858 --> 02:13:21.243 line:82%
Look at me.

1306
02:13:24.150 --> 02:13:29.861 line:82%
I understand your suffering
and impatience. Your tears.

1307
02:13:30.983 --> 02:13:33.944 line:82%
But can't you see?
This is only the beginning.

1308
02:13:34.566 --> 02:13:37.361 line:82%
No one knows me well here.

1309
02:13:38.525 --> 02:13:40.776 line:82%
I need more time, Simran.

1310
02:13:41.733 --> 02:13:46.319 line:82%
And I need you to be strong.
I need your laughter.

1311
02:13:48.691 --> 02:13:55.193 line:82%
No idiot can give you a ring
and take you away from me.

1312
02:13:56.858 --> 02:14:00.527 line:82%
You're mine. Only mine.

1313
02:14:08.566 --> 02:14:11.194 line:82%
Chutki will wake up. Go.
Hurry!

1314
02:14:13.441 --> 02:14:14.610 line:82%
Listen.

1315
02:14:38.155 --> 02:14:39.318 line:82%
Sister?

1316
02:14:41.736 --> 02:14:43.193 line:82%
Can I say something?

1317
02:14:45.275 --> 02:14:49.027 line:82%
I really don't like Kuljit.
Don't marry him.

1318
02:14:51.996 --> 02:14:54.003 line:82%
It's late. Go to sleep.

1319
02:14:58.766 --> 02:15:00.788 line:82%
I like the man on the roof.

1320
02:15:12.275 --> 02:15:15.445 line:82%
Isn't Raj the man you met
in Europe?

1321
02:15:22.109 --> 02:15:24.841 line:82%
I like him a lot. Marry him.

1322
02:15:26.608 --> 02:15:29.624 line:82%
Don't worry. I'll marry him.

1323
02:15:35.608 --> 02:15:36.818 line:82%
I love you, Sister.

1324
02:15:38.692 --> 02:15:42.111 line:82%
Give these almonds to Ramu
to add to the sherbet.

1325
02:15:44.066 --> 02:15:47.400 line:82%
- Where are the flowers?
- You left them by the stairs.

1326
02:15:47.483 --> 02:15:50.652 line:82%
I forgot. How would we
manage without you?

1327
02:15:51.525 --> 02:15:54.818 line:82%
The brave of heart will win
the bride.

1328
02:15:56.066 --> 02:15:59.997 line:82%
Weren't you on the groom's side?
When did you switch sides?

1329
02:16:00.080 --> 02:16:05.508 line:82%
Hey, pal. I'll get married one day,
so I'm practicing. Get it?

1330
02:16:05.591 --> 02:16:07.985 line:82%
- What the hell!
- Dimwit.

1331
02:16:26.986 --> 02:16:29.569 line:82%
What a lucky fellow Kuljit is!

1332
02:16:36.850 --> 02:16:38.694 line:82%
Now for the ring.

1333
02:16:42.733 --> 02:16:45.027 line:82%
Simran, your hand.

1334
02:16:46.192 --> 02:16:48.527 line:82%
Simran, your hand.

1335
02:16:58.788 --> 02:17:00.068 line:82%
What happened?

1336
02:17:00.892 --> 02:17:05.778 line:82%
I cut my fingers when I took
my bangles off.

1337
02:17:09.524 --> 02:17:10.529 line:82%
Never mind.

1338
02:17:10.816 --> 02:17:12.443 line:82%
The other hand, then.

1339
02:17:22.883 --> 02:17:26.693 line:82%
These girls make your head spin

1340
02:17:27.780 --> 02:17:31.335 line:82%
These boys are just street rascals

1341
02:17:49.983 --> 02:17:54.373 line:82%
Paint your hands with henna.
Decorate the bridal palanquin

1342
02:17:54.977 --> 02:17:59.356 line:82%
Paint your hands with henna.
Decorate the bridal palanquin

1343
02:17:59.946 --> 02:18:04.782 line:82%
Fair girl, your beloved
is coming to take you away

1344
02:18:21.817 --> 02:18:23.629 line:82%
Behind the groom's garland

1345
02:18:24.441 --> 02:18:26.235 line:82%
Hide your face

1346
02:18:31.733 --> 02:18:36.386 line:82%
Keep your feelings hidden
in your heart

1347
02:19:14.475 --> 02:19:19.274 line:82%
As your hair flies in the wind,
what is it trying to tell me?

1348
02:19:19.357 --> 02:19:23.275 line:82%
All these unmarried lovers wait,
heart in hand

1349
02:19:24.233 --> 02:19:29.025 line:82%
Hide the girls in the house,
out of modesty

1350
02:19:29.108 --> 02:19:33.481 line:82%
Our village is overrun by
crazy boys from the city

1351
02:19:33.861 --> 02:19:38.259 line:82%
Don't meet their eye.
Protect your modesty

1352
02:19:43.673 --> 02:19:47.583 line:82%
Fair girl, your beloved is coming
to take you away

1353
02:20:27.653 --> 02:20:32.277 line:82%
I'm a young man.
You're a beautiful girl

1354
02:20:32.633 --> 02:20:36.801 line:82%
If my heart skips a beat,
am I to blame?

1355
02:20:37.359 --> 02:20:42.102 line:82%
Hold onto your heart.
Beauty is sheer magic

1356
02:20:42.328 --> 02:20:46.769 line:82%
If it casts its spell,
am I to blame?

1357
02:20:47.113 --> 02:20:51.437 line:82%
Keep an eye out for me.
Leave the door ajar

1358
02:20:56.985 --> 02:21:01.840 line:82%
Fair girl, your beloved is coming
to take you away

1359
02:21:01.923 --> 02:21:05.862 line:82%
Say nothing more.
Do nothing more

1360
02:21:11.726 --> 02:21:15.819 line:82%
Hide your feelings in your heart

1361
02:22:29.228 --> 02:22:32.028 line:82%
My goddess of beauty

1362
02:22:33.798 --> 02:22:38.233 line:82%
My goddess of beauty,
how unaware you are

1363
02:22:38.316 --> 02:22:42.400 line:82%
That you're still beautiful,
and I am young

1364
02:22:42.693 --> 02:22:47.057 line:82%
I could give my life for you,
my love

1365
02:23:13.429 --> 02:23:18.039 line:82%
Paint your hands with henna.
Decorate the bridal palanquin

1366
02:24:27.983 --> 02:24:30.011 line:82%
Father, you were wonderful yesterday.

1367
02:24:30.288 --> 02:24:32.985 line:82%
How you danced!
Outdid them all.

1368
02:24:34.206 --> 02:24:36.027 line:82%
Good, very good.

1369
02:24:45.788 --> 02:24:49.152 line:82%
Just a bit of dirt. It's gone.

1370
02:24:55.310 --> 02:25:00.402 line:82%
Father, aren't there fewer
white doves today?

1371
02:25:03.114 --> 02:25:05.986 line:82%
One, two, three...

1372
02:25:08.173 --> 02:25:10.735 line:82%
No, maybe not.

1373
02:25:31.441 --> 02:25:32.899 line:82%
I've made up my mind.

1374
02:25:32.982 --> 02:25:37.152 line:82%
Today I'll talk to Raj.
Why be embarrassed?

1375
02:25:38.016 --> 02:25:40.854 line:82%
- Raj is here.
- Already?

1376
02:25:41.112 --> 02:25:44.819 line:82%
Raj, my dear boy!
Come and sit down.

1377
02:25:51.195 --> 02:25:55.069 line:82%
Raj, I have something
important to tell you.

1378
02:25:55.758 --> 02:25:58.986 line:82%
Usually this is discussed
with the elders.

1379
02:25:59.066 --> 02:26:03.403 line:82%
But we're so close,
why not talk directly?

1380
02:26:05.141 --> 02:26:08.866 line:82%
I want our friendship
to become kinship.

1381
02:26:09.081 --> 02:26:10.110 line:82%
Why not?

1382
02:26:10.193 --> 02:26:12.364 line:82%
My daughter Preeti...

1383
02:26:12.827 --> 02:26:15.650 line:82%
I want you to marry her.

1384
02:26:19.361 --> 02:26:23.577 line:82%
Raj, old boy, think fast or
you're done for.

1385
02:26:23.800 --> 02:26:25.943 line:82%
Raj, do you have any objections?

1386
02:26:27.400 --> 02:26:29.027 line:82%
How could I?

1387
02:26:32.066 --> 02:26:35.305 line:82%
But I can't decide on my own.
You'll have to talk to Pops.

1388
02:26:35.388 --> 02:26:37.068 line:82%
- Pops?
- My father.

1389
02:26:38.275 --> 02:26:40.609 line:82%
What a good boy he is!

1390
02:26:40.861 --> 02:26:42.947 line:82%
I never do anything
against his wishes.

1391
02:26:43.030 --> 02:26:47.652 line:82%
No problem. Give me his number.
I'll phone him.

1392
02:26:50.566 --> 02:26:53.569 line:82%
Actually, he's gone to America
on business.

1393
02:26:54.691 --> 02:26:58.681 line:82%
- I'll ask him to come here
- Why not?

1394
02:27:03.641 --> 02:27:06.400 line:82%
My country! My soil!

1395
02:27:06.483 --> 02:27:09.027 line:82%
Raj, my son. Here I am!

1396
02:27:11.673 --> 02:27:15.110 line:82%
You can find everything
outside of India.

1397
02:27:15.316 --> 02:27:17.944 line:82%
But not your wife's great cooking.

1398
02:27:18.650 --> 02:27:21.515 line:82%
Or our language and culture.

1399
02:27:21.598 --> 02:27:25.403 line:82%
When you love the Ganges,
how can the Thames move you?

1400
02:27:25.705 --> 02:27:29.777 line:82%
I told Raj, "Come back only
when you're married."

1401
02:27:30.566 --> 02:27:33.403 line:82%
Anyway, what do you do
in London?

1402
02:27:34.316 --> 02:27:36.358 line:82%
- In London?
- Forget London.

1403
02:27:36.441 --> 02:27:40.152 line:82%
My philosophy is "Go East,
go West. Punjab is the best."

1404
02:27:47.048 --> 02:27:50.233 line:82%
Don't worry. All is well.
They're very innocent.

1405
02:27:50.316 --> 02:27:52.568 line:82%
I missed you, my son.

1406
02:27:55.691 --> 02:27:57.952 line:82%
You didn't say your daddy
was here?

1407
02:27:58.185 --> 02:28:02.900 line:82%
A miracle! We were talking about
him and I met him at the bazaar.

1408
02:28:02.983 --> 02:28:05.425 line:82%
He had your photo and was looking
for you.

1409
02:28:05.508 --> 02:28:10.361 line:82%
I knew it!
The Lord wants this marriage.

1410
02:28:11.138 --> 02:28:13.150 line:82%
- My in-law.
- In-law?

1411
02:28:13.233 --> 02:28:16.892 line:82%
Of course! Why do you need me to
approve a good deed?

1412
02:28:16.975 --> 02:28:19.650 line:82%
Have I ever refused you anything?

1413
02:28:19.733 --> 02:28:22.443 line:82%
Let's sweeten your
son-in-law's mouth.

1414
02:28:22.983 --> 02:28:26.297 line:82%
Let them marry at once.
Never delay a good deed.

1415
02:28:26.380 --> 02:28:30.235 line:82%
Terrific!
We'll have a double wedding.

1416
02:28:30.775 --> 02:28:32.027 line:82%
So it's settled!

1417
02:28:37.396 --> 02:28:40.027 line:82%
- Happy?
- Yes, Pops.

1418
02:28:40.525 --> 02:28:44.068 line:82%
Let's celebrate.
My son is happy.

1419
02:28:47.038 --> 02:28:52.441 line:82%
So you're marrying Preeti and
Kuljit is Preeti's brother.

1420
02:28:52.524 --> 02:28:55.193 line:82%
And Kuljit is marrying Simran.

1421
02:28:55.815 --> 02:28:59.067 line:82%
But you love Simran, not Preeti.

1422
02:28:59.150 --> 02:29:02.943 line:82%
- So why was Preeti in London?
- Not Preeti. Simran.

1423
02:29:04.275 --> 02:29:05.858 line:82%
Who's Simran?

1424
02:29:05.941 --> 02:29:09.569 line:82%
- Pops, please stop thinking.
- I need to.

1425
02:29:11.094 --> 02:29:14.197 line:82%
Don't worry. I'm here.
I'll sort things out.

1426
02:29:14.280 --> 02:29:17.275 line:82%
Thank you, Pops.
Just like you've done already.

1427
02:29:17.358 --> 02:29:20.692 line:82%
"Let them marry at once.
Never delay a good deed."

1428
02:29:20.775 --> 02:29:24.611 line:82%
- Pops, why did you come?
- I was missing you, son.

1429
02:29:27.673 --> 02:29:30.525 line:82%
OK, I made a mistake. I'll fix it.

1430
02:29:30.608 --> 02:29:35.778 line:82%
I'll say it's the anniversary of
your mother's death, so no wedding.

1431
02:29:38.278 --> 02:29:40.606 line:82%
- Preeti!
- May I come in?

1432
02:29:40.689 --> 02:29:44.482 line:82%
Of course. You will have
a long life.

1433
02:29:44.565 --> 02:29:48.070 line:82%
Raj and I were just talking
about you.

1434
02:29:50.090 --> 02:29:52.319 line:82%
Milk? For me?

1435
02:29:52.830 --> 02:29:55.569 line:82%
Tomorrow is Karwa Chauth.

1436
02:29:56.733 --> 02:29:59.608 line:82%
Can I fast for my future husband?

1437
02:29:59.691 --> 02:30:02.778 line:82%
- Of course. What's the problem?
- A fast for husbands, Pops.

1438
02:30:03.361 --> 02:30:06.819 line:82%
- Oh, no! Never.
- Why not?

1439
02:30:08.151 --> 02:30:12.025 line:82%
In our family, girls fasting before
marriage brings bad luck.

1440
02:30:12.108 --> 02:30:17.194 line:82%
Besides, we can't discuss
the wedding for a month.

1441
02:30:17.441 --> 02:30:22.820 line:82%
This month is the anniversary of
my wife's death.

1442
02:30:23.858 --> 02:30:28.069 line:82%
It's not the right time.
Let's talk to your father.

1443
02:30:35.433 --> 02:30:36.523 line:82%
Simran!

1444
02:30:40.695 --> 02:30:43.994 line:82%
Raj, do you know what tomorrow is?

1445
02:30:46.508 --> 02:30:47.523 line:82%
What now?

1446
02:30:49.215 --> 02:30:51.485 line:82%
My first Karwa Chauth.

1447
02:30:51.995 --> 02:30:56.692 line:82%
I want you to give me a drop of
water and a morsel of food

1448
02:30:56.775 --> 02:30:58.084 line:82%
so I can break the fast.

1449
02:30:58.310 --> 02:31:00.016 line:82%
- Hands off.
- Why?

1450
02:31:00.210 --> 02:31:01.776 line:82%
I said, "hands off."

1451
02:31:05.581 --> 02:31:09.612 line:82%
If you don't love me, just say so
and I will go away quietly.

1452
02:31:09.695 --> 02:31:14.065 line:82%
Then you can marry Kuljit and I'll
be spared these daily scenes.

1453
02:31:14.381 --> 02:31:18.819 line:82%
- Did I say something wrong?
- No, impossible.

1454
02:31:19.233 --> 02:31:23.400 line:82%
"I want you to give me a drop of
water and a morsel of food

1455
02:31:23.483 --> 02:31:24.840 line:82%
to break the fast."

1456
02:31:24.923 --> 02:31:27.455 line:82%
Are you nuts? I say publicly:

1457
02:31:27.538 --> 02:31:31.901 line:82%
"Hi, Simran. I'm your future
husband. Drink the water."

1458
02:31:32.415 --> 02:31:33.592 line:82%
I'll starve to death.

1459
02:31:33.675 --> 02:31:37.525 line:82%
But I'll only take water
and food from you.

1460
02:31:42.663 --> 02:31:44.360 line:82%
Like father, like daughter.

1461
02:31:52.163 --> 02:31:54.193 line:82%
Mr. Malhotra, you're amazing.

1462
02:31:54.891 --> 02:31:58.358 line:82%
No one would guess you're Indian
judging by your clothes.

1463
02:31:58.631 --> 02:32:04.062 line:82%
Don't be fooled by appearances.
I carry India deep in my heart.

1464
02:32:04.301 --> 02:32:08.845 line:82%
Bravo! Such fine thoughts!

1465
02:32:11.611 --> 02:32:15.297 line:82%
I believe you want to start
a factory here.

1466
02:32:15.820 --> 02:32:18.269 line:82%
The factory is just an excuse.

1467
02:32:18.505 --> 02:32:21.678 line:82%
The truth is I came looking
for a wife for Raj.

1468
02:32:23.080 --> 02:32:26.276 line:82%
All the men are hiding behind
the house.

1469
02:32:26.943 --> 02:32:30.610 line:82%
They say today's women's day.
So we can't disturb them.

1470
02:32:31.276 --> 02:32:34.568 line:82%
Are you fasting too, darling?

1471
02:32:38.308 --> 02:32:39.985 line:82%
May you live long, child.

1472
02:32:40.371 --> 02:32:44.402 line:82%
My son is blessed to have
a bride like you.

1473
02:32:46.745 --> 02:32:48.486 line:82%
Careful, children.

1474
02:32:50.175 --> 02:32:52.610 line:82%
This is Pops. I mean, my father.

1475
02:32:54.558 --> 02:32:59.069 line:82%
- Raj has enchanted us all.
- Like father, like son.

1476
02:33:00.631 --> 02:33:02.318 line:82%
I'll be right back.

1477
02:33:06.278 --> 02:33:08.011 line:82%
- Pops, this is...
- I know.

1478
02:33:09.486 --> 02:33:10.968 line:82%
This can only be Simran.

1479
02:33:23.830 --> 02:33:24.986 line:82%
Beautiful.

1480
02:33:25.851 --> 02:33:26.936 line:82%
Bless you.

1481
02:33:31.185 --> 02:33:33.860 line:82%
- Pops?
- Excellent, fantastic done. Let's go.

1482
02:33:39.816 --> 02:33:43.069 line:82%
Watch where you're going.
The flowers...

1483
02:33:47.288 --> 02:33:48.527 line:82%
I am sorry.

1484
02:33:49.441 --> 02:33:53.650 line:82%
Oh spring! Shower us with flowers

1485
02:33:53.733 --> 02:33:57.987 line:82%
My beloved is here

1486
02:34:14.151 --> 02:34:16.861 line:82%
Kammo, where are the flowers?
Hurry.

1487
02:34:19.507 --> 02:34:20.693 line:82%
Excuse me.

1488
02:34:22.110 --> 02:34:24.862 line:82%
I'm Raj's father, from London.

1489
02:34:26.183 --> 02:34:30.279 line:82%
Born in Bhatinda but lived in
London for years. And you?

1490
02:34:31.418 --> 02:34:33.736 line:82%
- I'm Simran's aunt.
- Impossible!

1491
02:34:34.171 --> 02:34:36.277 line:82%
You look like her sister.

1492
02:34:39.193 --> 02:34:41.444 line:82%
Aren't you fasting?

1493
02:34:42.983 --> 02:34:46.194 line:82%
- I'm not married.
- That's great news.

1494
02:34:47.066 --> 02:34:48.611 line:82%
Your flower.

1495
02:34:49.858 --> 02:34:54.403 line:82%
Perhaps it was meant for you.
You keep it.

1496
02:35:07.705 --> 02:35:11.817 line:82%
Raj, when will the moon rise?
I'm starving.

1497
02:35:11.900 --> 02:35:14.317 line:82%
Starving? I told you not to fast.

1498
02:35:20.766 --> 02:35:23.235 line:82%
Eat, no one's watching.

1499
02:35:23.715 --> 02:35:25.873 line:82%
- Stop it!
- Don't eat.

1500
02:35:28.705 --> 02:35:32.776 line:82%
Hey, Simran. The moon is out.
Look over there.

1501
02:36:02.275 --> 02:36:05.696 line:82%
In her eyes, a prayer

1502
02:36:07.455 --> 02:36:11.321 line:82%
A prayer for her husband's
long life

1503
02:36:13.733 --> 02:36:18.862 line:82%
To see the moon,
I fold my hands in prayer

1504
02:36:19.066 --> 02:36:23.047 line:82%
To break the fast of
Karwa Chauth

1505
02:36:25.888 --> 02:36:31.642 line:82%
When I drink the water you offer,
this devotee will become your queen

1506
02:36:31.725 --> 02:36:36.730 line:82%
Whatever you pray for tonight
will be yours

1507
02:36:36.933 --> 02:36:41.929 line:82%
Oh stranger, come home.
Your country is calling you

1508
02:36:53.873 --> 02:36:56.653 line:82%
What's wrong?
Hurry, some water.

1509
02:37:02.703 --> 02:37:05.703 line:82%
- What's wrong?
- She was a bit dizzy.

1510
02:37:06.640 --> 02:37:09.445 line:82%
Come, child.

1511
02:37:12.191 --> 02:37:15.486 line:82%
- What happened?
- She was just a little dizzy.

1512
02:37:17.423 --> 02:37:20.351 line:82%
Come on, brothers. Let's eat.

1513
02:37:22.746 --> 02:37:25.111 line:82%
She's so delicate, poor thing.

1514
02:37:27.526 --> 02:37:29.812 line:82%
What's wrong?
Are you fasting, too?

1515
02:37:30.068 --> 02:37:32.437 line:82%
- No way.
- Then come along.

1516
02:37:34.006 --> 02:37:36.557 line:82%
It isn't easy for him to come.

1517
02:37:36.640 --> 02:37:41.153 line:82%
They don't let Raj out of their sight.

1518
02:37:41.466 --> 02:37:44.983 line:82%
He won't come. Please, eat.

1519
02:37:45.066 --> 02:37:47.736 line:82%
No. I'd rather starve to death.

1520
02:37:48.433 --> 02:37:51.069 line:82%
Very well, then.
Don't eat. Die.

1521
02:37:58.816 --> 02:38:00.819 line:82%
I am sorry. Hi, Chutki.

1522
02:38:01.016 --> 02:38:05.233 line:82%
Sorry, I'm late. What could I do?
They wouldn't let me go.

1523
02:38:05.316 --> 02:38:08.862 line:82%
It was hell getting away.
Please eat.

1524
02:38:09.225 --> 02:38:10.610 line:82%
Eat, Sister.

1525
02:38:13.631 --> 02:38:18.153 line:82%
I said I'm sorry. Now eat
or you'll faint for real.

1526
02:38:21.643 --> 02:38:26.569 line:82%
Chutki, please tell him
not to worry about me.

1527
02:38:27.141 --> 02:38:29.608 line:82%
When I was dying of hunger.

1528
02:38:29.691 --> 02:38:33.653 line:82%
he was eating to
his heart's content.

1529
02:38:34.308 --> 02:38:37.233 line:82%
Besides, it's my first
Karwa Chauth.

1530
02:38:37.316 --> 02:38:41.486 line:82%
Is he bothered? What's it to him
if I live or die?

1531
02:38:41.725 --> 02:38:46.234 line:82%
Oh God, Sister. Raj hasn't
eaten since this morning.

1532
02:38:46.725 --> 02:38:51.942 line:82%
He said he'd eat with you, and
made me promise not to tell.

1533
02:38:52.025 --> 02:38:54.590 line:82%
Sorry, Raj. I couldn't keep quiet
any longer.

1534
02:39:04.871 --> 02:39:05.985 line:82%
Come here.

1535
02:39:07.400 --> 02:39:08.985 line:82%
Are you talking to me?

1536
02:39:26.663 --> 02:39:30.609 line:82%
- I said too much in anger.
- Don't worry, Senorita.

1537
02:39:31.080 --> 02:39:34.695 line:82%
In big countries such small
things do happen.

1538
02:39:41.755 --> 02:39:44.344 line:82%
It's my turn. You feed me now.

1539
02:40:04.601 --> 02:40:07.652 line:82%
I told you not to betray me.

1540
02:40:15.288 --> 02:40:18.382 line:82%
My daughter will not suffer
what I suffered.

1541
02:40:18.465 --> 02:40:23.017 line:82%
She will not make sacrifices either
as a daughter, sister or wife.

1542
02:40:23.100 --> 02:40:27.044 line:82%
She'll live her life as she pleases.
Find happiness.

1543
02:40:33.232 --> 02:40:34.318 line:82%
Come in.

1544
02:41:00.478 --> 02:41:01.609 line:82%
Take this.

1545
02:41:03.275 --> 02:41:04.860 line:82%
I won't hear a word.

1546
02:41:05.858 --> 02:41:10.237 line:82%
I know everything. I've seen
everything I need to see.

1547
02:41:11.570 --> 02:41:14.146 line:82%
I know Raj is the boy
you met in Europe.

1548
02:41:14.983 --> 02:41:17.923 line:82%
I also know you love each other
very much.

1549
02:41:18.858 --> 02:41:20.570 line:82%
I was wrong, Simran.

1550
02:41:21.381 --> 02:41:27.104 line:82%
My daughter will not sacrifice
her happiness or her love.

1551
02:41:30.400 --> 02:41:34.444 line:82%
Raj, I know you'll make
her happy.

1552
02:41:35.520 --> 02:41:39.327 line:82%
You both have my blessings.
Take my daughter away.

1553
02:41:39.860 --> 02:41:40.973 line:82%
Go away.

1554
02:41:41.816 --> 02:41:44.819 line:82%
No one here will understand
your love.

1555
02:41:45.941 --> 02:41:47.023 line:82%
Take her away.

1556
02:41:48.631 --> 02:41:50.193 line:82%
I'll take care of things here.

1557
02:41:50.987 --> 02:41:53.027 line:82%
I won't hear a word.

1558
02:41:53.566 --> 02:41:57.277 line:82%
Go, before I weaken.

1559
02:41:58.400 --> 02:42:00.453 line:82%
Please go.

1560
02:42:01.025 --> 02:42:05.528 line:82%
- I implore you, take her away.
- I'll take her away, Maaji.

1561
02:42:10.131 --> 02:42:11.819 line:82%
Please sit, Maaji.

1562
02:42:14.233 --> 02:42:15.610 line:82%
Here.

1563
02:42:20.941 --> 02:42:23.527 line:82%
I was very young when
my mother died.

1564
02:42:24.691 --> 02:42:27.611 line:82%
But I owe what I am today
to her.

1565
02:42:28.550 --> 02:42:31.819 line:82%
She told me something
I've never forgotten.

1566
02:42:32.538 --> 02:42:38.153 line:82%
She said: "Son, at every turn
in life, you'll find two paths.

1567
02:42:38.581 --> 02:42:41.152 line:82%
The right and the wrong path.

1568
02:42:42.048 --> 02:42:45.945 line:82%
The wrong path is the easy one.
It'll draw you to it.

1569
02:42:46.525 --> 02:42:50.944 line:82%
The right path will be strewn
with difficulties.

1570
02:42:52.441 --> 02:42:54.652 line:82%
If you take the wrong path,

1571
02:42:55.233 --> 02:42:59.153 line:82%
at first you'll be rewarded
with success and joy.

1572
02:43:00.183 --> 02:43:03.528 line:82%
But in the end, you'll be
the loser.

1573
02:43:04.590 --> 02:43:06.861 line:82%
If you take the right path

1574
02:43:07.818 --> 02:43:13.069 line:82%
at every step you'll be faced
with hardship and trouble.

1575
02:43:14.580 --> 02:43:18.652 line:82%
But in the end, you'll be
the winner."

1576
02:43:22.066 --> 02:43:23.610 line:82%
Tell me, Maaji.

1577
02:43:25.080 --> 02:43:29.537 line:82%
Is my path the right one
or the wrong one?

1578
02:43:33.631 --> 02:43:36.111 line:82%
Yours is the right path, son.

1579
02:43:37.766 --> 02:43:39.791 line:82%
But you don't know my husband.

1580
02:43:42.174 --> 02:43:46.619 line:82%
Maaji, your husband doesn't
know me.

1581
02:43:48.775 --> 02:43:53.987 line:82%
If I'd wanted to elope with Simran,
I'd have done it by now.

1582
02:43:55.433 --> 02:43:59.694 line:82%
But I don't want to snatch her away.
I want to win her.

1583
02:44:00.566 --> 02:44:05.487 line:82%
I don't want to steal her. I want us
to leave with our heads held high.

1584
02:44:06.441 --> 02:44:11.362 line:82%
Now I'm here, I'll take my bride
away with me.

1585
02:44:12.316 --> 02:44:13.987 line:82%
But I'll only leave

1586
02:44:14.775 --> 02:44:19.737 line:82%
when her father gives me
her hand.

1587
02:44:21.558 --> 02:44:24.986 line:82%
Simran is not your problem
any more. She's mine.

1588
02:44:25.691 --> 02:44:28.570 line:82%
You've said goodbye to
your daughter.

1589
02:44:29.415 --> 02:44:33.168 line:82%
Now let the bridal palanquin depart.

1590
02:44:44.650 --> 02:44:46.201 line:82%
Excuse me.

1591
02:44:46.284 --> 02:44:50.485 line:82%
Does this crying disorder
run in the family?

1592
02:44:59.923 --> 02:45:01.609 line:82%
Good shot, my God.

1593
02:45:02.038 --> 02:45:04.740 line:82%
Kuljeet, now that we are friends

1594
02:45:04.823 --> 02:45:06.642 line:82%
I hope you won't mind if I tell
you something.

1595
02:45:06.725 --> 02:45:08.560 line:82%
Go ahead, Uncle.

1596
02:45:08.643 --> 02:45:12.858 line:82%
That girl... what's her name?
Ah, Simran!

1597
02:45:12.941 --> 02:45:16.085 line:82%
You're not a good match,
to be very frank with you.

1598
02:45:16.168 --> 02:45:20.032 line:82%
- Why not, Uncle?
- She doesn't deserve you.

1599
02:45:20.115 --> 02:45:23.797 line:82%
You're a strong young man
from Punjab.

1600
02:45:23.880 --> 02:45:28.678 line:82%
That girl is too quiet and shy.
Not a good match.

1601
02:45:29.108 --> 02:45:32.692 line:82%
You need a feisty girl.
Real feisty.

1602
02:45:32.775 --> 02:45:37.985 line:82%
Come to London. I'll introduce you
to real sparklers. You'll go nuts.

1603
02:45:39.316 --> 02:45:41.259 line:82%
No problem, Uncle.

1604
02:45:41.405 --> 02:45:44.692 line:82%
After I marry Simran
she'll stay here

1605
02:45:44.775 --> 02:45:48.944 line:82%
and I'll come to London
to meet the sparklers.

1606
02:45:50.840 --> 02:45:53.400 line:82%
Two birds, one in hand, one in the bush.

1607
02:45:53.483 --> 02:45:58.071 line:82%
- We'll raise hell.
- Like hell you will, you fool!

1608
02:46:04.195 --> 02:46:09.027 line:82%
I was very young when my father
sat me on his shoulders

1609
02:46:09.691 --> 02:46:12.194 line:82%
and brought me to these fields.

1610
02:46:13.400 --> 02:46:16.278 line:82%
I've been friends with
the pigeons ever since.

1611
02:46:17.661 --> 02:46:20.110 line:82%
I feel at peace here.

1612
02:46:21.358 --> 02:46:26.318 line:82%
I love spending time
with these pigeons.

1613
02:46:28.151 --> 02:46:30.028 line:82%
Tell me something, Father.

1614
02:46:30.830 --> 02:46:35.444 line:82%
Are these pigeons different
from the ones in London?

1615
02:46:41.041 --> 02:46:42.694 line:82%
There's a difference.

1616
02:46:43.310 --> 02:46:48.403 line:82%
These pigeons know me.
They belong to my land.

1617
02:46:49.445 --> 02:46:52.111 line:82%
In London, they're strangers.

1618
02:46:52.816 --> 02:46:57.361 line:82%
Maybe the difference lies
in your perception.

1619
02:46:59.441 --> 02:47:03.944 line:82%
One of those London pigeons
might have flown from here.

1620
02:47:04.558 --> 02:47:09.551 line:82%
It comes from your land.
It knows you.

1621
02:47:11.735 --> 02:47:13.816 line:82%
But perhaps you can't
recognize it.

1622
02:47:23.550 --> 02:47:24.735 line:82%
What's happened?

1623
02:47:29.300 --> 02:47:30.777 line:82%
What are you doing?

1624
02:47:31.871 --> 02:47:37.236 line:82%
My mother always said our country's
soil is very strong. It'll be fine.

1625
02:47:37.923 --> 02:47:40.903 line:82%
But who did this insane thing?

1626
02:47:44.330 --> 02:47:45.490 line:82%
Kuljit?

1627
02:47:45.806 --> 02:47:48.809 line:82%
Look, Father.

1628
02:47:56.018 --> 02:47:57.235 line:82%
Let's go.

1629
02:48:00.413 --> 02:48:03.152 line:82%
Are you still angry about
that beer incident?

1630
02:48:05.391 --> 02:48:08.952 line:82%
It was a folly of youth.
Forgive me.

1631
02:48:10.983 --> 02:48:12.690 line:82%
I've forgotten all about it.

1632
02:48:14.245 --> 02:48:16.569 line:82%
I was wrong about you.

1633
02:48:17.361 --> 02:48:21.924 line:82%
You're right. Maybe I didn't
recognize it.

1634
02:48:28.066 --> 02:48:29.195 line:82%
Sorry.

1635
02:48:34.820 --> 02:48:40.153 line:82%
What's wrong, Mother? You called me.

1636
02:48:43.280 --> 02:48:47.075 line:82%
The doctor may say what he wants,

1637
02:48:47.886 --> 02:48:50.151 line:82%
but I know my time is up.

1638
02:48:50.683 --> 02:48:54.483 line:82%
Don't say such inauspicious things,
Mother.

1639
02:48:54.566 --> 02:48:59.111 line:82%
Nothing to worry about.
It's time to leave.

1640
02:49:03.550 --> 02:49:05.986 line:82%
I've had a wonderful life.

1641
02:49:08.475 --> 02:49:11.153 line:82%
I have no complaints, dear.

1642
02:49:12.108 --> 02:49:15.986 line:82%
But now that I've seen Simran

1643
02:49:17.066 --> 02:49:21.486 line:82%
a wish fills my heart.

1644
02:49:23.601 --> 02:49:27.861 line:82%
I want to see my granddaughter
as a bride.

1645
02:49:29.131 --> 02:49:32.986 line:82%
I hope I don't die
before she marries.

1646
02:49:33.266 --> 02:49:36.445 line:82%
Don't say that, Mother.

1647
02:49:40.465 --> 02:49:42.278 line:82%
The bridal palanquin

1648
02:49:42.483 --> 02:49:45.486 line:82%
needs only to go from one
neighboring house to another.

1649
02:49:45.941 --> 02:49:48.111 line:82%
And you're all here with me.

1650
02:49:48.955 --> 02:49:54.640 line:82%
Don't wait another week.
Can't they marry tomorrow?

1651
02:49:54.893 --> 02:49:58.894 line:82%
You're right. Let them
marry tomorrow.

1652
02:49:58.977 --> 02:50:01.010 line:82%
Isn't it, Baldev? The wedding
procession will come tomorrow.

1653
02:50:01.093 --> 02:50:02.238 line:82%
- Yes, Mom.
- Tomorrow.

1654
02:50:02.321 --> 02:50:03.628 line:82%
It'll come tomorrow only.

1655
02:50:13.816 --> 02:50:15.511 line:82%
We must take Simran away.

1656
02:50:18.153 --> 02:50:19.777 line:82%
There's no other way.

1657
02:50:20.941 --> 02:50:23.110 line:82%
I've got it all planned.

1658
02:50:23.381 --> 02:50:25.330 line:82%
We'll take the morning train.

1659
02:50:25.735 --> 02:50:30.233 line:82%
I'll get the tickets and wait
for you. Bring Simran somehow.

1660
02:50:30.316 --> 02:50:32.027 line:82%
We'll face whatever happens later.

1661
02:50:33.550 --> 02:50:34.818 line:82%
Are you listening?

1662
02:50:36.591 --> 02:50:40.818 line:82%
I know you don't want to
take Simran like this.

1663
02:50:41.316 --> 02:50:42.985 line:82%
But it's too late now.

1664
02:50:43.476 --> 02:50:47.319 line:82%
If you love her and want
to marry her

1665
02:50:47.566 --> 02:50:50.777 line:82%
you'll have to elope, understand?

1666
02:50:52.650 --> 02:50:53.652 line:82%
Good.

1667
02:50:59.233 --> 02:51:01.565 line:82%
Take me away from here, Raj.

1668
02:51:01.891 --> 02:51:06.495 line:82%
You don't know my father, Raj.
We'll have to elope.

1669
02:51:07.141 --> 02:51:09.693 line:82%
I came here to make you
my bride.

1670
02:51:10.090 --> 02:51:14.971 line:82%
I'll only take you away when
your father gives me your hand.

1671
02:51:15.775 --> 02:51:18.569 line:82%
I don't know what will
happen tomorrow.

1672
02:51:22.399 --> 02:51:26.527 line:82%
I myself don't know what
I'm going to do.

1673
02:51:30.400 --> 02:51:33.027 line:82%
But you'll have to trust me.

1674
02:51:36.816 --> 02:51:38.860 line:82%
Whatever I do tomorrow

1675
02:51:42.233 --> 02:51:43.705 line:82%
it'll be for both of us.

1676
02:51:49.766 --> 02:51:50.912 line:82%
Do you love me?

1677
02:51:53.858 --> 02:51:55.079 line:82%
Do you trust me?

1678
02:51:58.685 --> 02:52:03.027 line:82%
All that's left is for the bridal
palanquin to depart.

1679
02:52:13.108 --> 02:52:16.949 line:82%
Oh, my friend

1680
02:52:21.025 --> 02:52:23.612 line:82%
Oh, my love

1681
02:52:29.525 --> 02:52:32.195 line:82%
I give you

1682
02:52:36.316 --> 02:52:40.364 line:82%
into the hands of God

1683
02:53:00.108 --> 02:53:02.650 line:82%
How strange are the ways
of the world

1684
02:53:02.733 --> 02:53:05.808 line:82%
How many blows our crazy hearts
must suffer

1685
02:53:05.891 --> 02:53:11.050 line:82%
What is left for me to hear or say?
Let our feelings stay unspoken

1686
02:53:15.650 --> 02:53:18.192 line:82%
No more hide and seek

1687
02:53:18.275 --> 02:53:21.152 line:82%
Tomorrow my bridal palanquin
will depart

1688
02:53:26.650 --> 02:53:31.403 line:82%
Is it the start or end of life?

1689
02:53:31.691 --> 02:53:36.694 line:82%
Simi, come. It's time for
the Mehndi ceremony.

1690
02:55:08.644 --> 02:55:12.692 line:82%
Father, I was going to tell you...

1691
02:55:15.983 --> 02:55:21.204 line:82%
You were right. It was I
who didn't recognize you.

1692
02:55:23.580 --> 02:55:25.860 line:82%
You've snuck into my home.

1693
02:55:26.650 --> 02:55:28.861 line:82%
Among my family.

1694
02:55:29.566 --> 02:55:32.204 line:82%
And played with my honor.

1695
02:55:33.818 --> 02:55:35.860 line:82%
You deceived me.

1696
02:55:36.275 --> 02:55:38.319 line:82%
You abused my trust.

1697
02:55:39.025 --> 02:55:41.309 line:82%
You mocked our decency.

1698
02:55:42.983 --> 02:55:46.317 line:82%
How dare you love Simran?

1699
02:55:46.400 --> 02:55:51.395 line:82%
How can you be worthy of her when
you're unworthy yourself?

1700
02:55:53.691 --> 02:55:56.275 line:82%
I was right about you.

1701
02:55:56.358 --> 02:56:00.650 line:82%
Scoundrels and liars like you
never change. They get worse.

1702
02:56:13.858 --> 02:56:16.442 line:82%
Didn't I tell you to
take me away?

1703
02:56:16.525 --> 02:56:19.694 line:82%
Didn't I say no one here
would understand our love?

1704
02:56:20.150 --> 02:56:22.068 line:82%
Didn't I tell you we must run?

1705
02:56:22.151 --> 02:56:25.002 line:82%
No, Simran. No.

1706
02:56:26.108 --> 02:56:28.234 line:82%
You can run away from strangers.

1707
02:56:29.892 --> 02:56:33.903 line:82%
But if you run away from your own,
where would you run to?

1708
02:56:40.459 --> 02:56:42.401 line:82%
They're our elders.

1709
02:56:43.621 --> 02:56:45.193 line:82%
Our parents.

1710
02:56:47.358 --> 02:56:50.902 line:82%
They spend their lives
raising us.

1711
02:56:51.816 --> 02:56:54.236 line:82%
They give us boundless love.

1712
02:56:56.150 --> 02:56:59.777 line:82%
They can decide things for us
better then we can.

1713
02:57:01.608 --> 02:57:07.386 line:82%
We've no right to make them suffer
for the sake of our happiness.

1714
02:57:13.941 --> 02:57:15.777 line:82%
Father is right.

1715
02:57:17.858 --> 02:57:21.569 line:82%
I'm a liar and a cheat.

1716
02:57:24.775 --> 02:57:28.319 line:82%
So what if I lied to win you?

1717
02:57:29.983 --> 02:57:32.361 line:82%
A lie is still a lie.

1718
02:57:36.066 --> 02:57:37.777 line:82%
Father is right.

1719
02:57:40.233 --> 02:57:42.068 line:82%
I'm unworthy of you.

1720
02:57:44.858 --> 02:57:48.943 line:82%
So what if I see no one else
but you?

1721
02:57:51.275 --> 02:57:55.527 line:82%
So what if yours is the only name
I recall?

1722
02:57:57.525 --> 02:58:01.652 line:82%
Father is right. I am a good-for-nothing.

1723
02:58:04.066 --> 02:58:07.611 line:82%
How did I imagine that
I could marry you?

1724
02:58:09.942 --> 02:58:13.902 line:82%
So what if this good-for-nothing
loves you madly?

1725
02:58:23.400 --> 02:58:25.137 line:82%
Love isn't everything.

1726
02:58:29.191 --> 02:58:31.069 line:82%
Father is right, Simran.

1727
02:58:33.191 --> 02:58:34.443 line:82%
Father is right.

1728
02:58:42.096 --> 02:58:46.819 line:82%
Here, Father.
I return what's yours.

1729
02:59:00.608 --> 02:59:04.027 line:82%
I didn't come here to break
anyone's heart.

1730
02:59:05.900 --> 02:59:07.943 line:82%
I came to win a heart.

1731
02:59:11.525 --> 02:59:14.194 line:82%
There must be something
lacking in me

1732
02:59:14.441 --> 02:59:16.777 line:82%
if I couldn't win your heart.

1733
02:59:19.983 --> 02:59:24.153 line:82%
If you think Kuljit will make
Simran happier than I can,

1734
02:59:28.733 --> 02:59:30.443 line:82%
then you must be right.

1735
02:59:32.816 --> 02:59:37.648 line:82%
You, better than anyone,
know what's best for Simran.

1736
02:59:42.150 --> 02:59:45.610 line:82%
Forgive me, Father.

1737
03:00:43.941 --> 03:00:45.902 line:82%
Forgive me, Preeti.

1738
03:00:47.525 --> 03:00:49.763 line:82%
I know I hurt you.

1739
03:01:43.025 --> 03:01:46.027 line:82%
Raj, where is Simran?

1740
03:01:49.191 --> 03:01:50.860 line:82%
She will come, Pops.

1741
03:01:54.900 --> 03:01:56.729 line:82%
Her father will bring her.

1742
03:01:57.816 --> 03:01:59.902 line:82%
He'll have to.

1743
03:02:24.775 --> 03:02:29.027 line:82%
I won't hear another word.
Go away.

1744
03:02:29.566 --> 03:02:33.902 line:82%
Your son has deceived us all.
Showed us his true colors.

1745
03:02:34.108 --> 03:02:37.243 line:82%
- I won't let a liar...
- Enough!

1746
03:02:40.608 --> 03:02:42.610 line:82%
My son is my pride.

1747
03:02:43.316 --> 03:02:44.988 line:82%
Don't insult my pride.

1748
03:04:02.108 --> 03:04:08.194 line:82%
They're fighting at the station.
Someone might get killed.

1749
03:04:08.485 --> 03:04:10.652 line:82%
Stop them. Please come.

1750
03:04:18.983 --> 03:04:21.021 line:82%
Simran, come with me.

1751
03:05:14.275 --> 03:05:15.777 line:82%
Stop it!

1752
03:06:52.858 --> 03:06:55.916 line:82%
Let me go, Father. Let me go.

1753
03:06:59.398 --> 03:07:03.568 line:82%
Raj is my life, Father.
I can't live without him.

1754
03:07:03.900 --> 03:07:05.990 line:82%
Let me go to my Raj.

1755
03:07:10.358 --> 03:07:12.569 line:82%
Father, please I beg of you.

1756
03:07:31.233 --> 03:07:32.557 line:82%
Go, Simran.

1757
03:07:34.900 --> 03:07:40.065 line:82%
No one could ever love you
more than this boy.

1758
03:07:41.316 --> 03:07:43.069 line:82%
Go, child. Go.

1759
03:07:43.608 --> 03:07:45.257 line:82%
Go to your Raj.

1760
03:07:46.150 --> 03:07:47.350 line:82%
Go, Simran.

1761
03:07:47.698 --> 03:07:49.412 line:82%
Go, live your life.

1762
03:08:49.734 --> 03:08:52.527 line:82%
- I am sorry.
- It's alright, Senorita.

1763
03:08:53.071 --> 03:08:56.902 line:82%
In big countries such small things
do happen.

1764
03:09:00.399 --> 03:09:05.527 line:82%
The brave of heart always win
the bride.

1765
03:09:08.650 --> 03:09:12.007 line:82%
When I saw you I knew,
my beloved

1766
03:09:13.733 --> 03:09:16.448 line:82%
Love is a crazy thing

1767
03:09:28.607 --> 03:09:31.688 line:82%
Where do I go from here?

1768
03:09:33.956 --> 03:09:38.777 line:82%
I could just die in your arms

